'''Bonnie Burton''' is a former Content Developer for [[Lucas Online]], [[StarWars.com]] Senior Editor, staff writer for ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine, and lead writer for The Official Star Wars Blog. Outside of the ''Star Wars'' world, Burton is the founder of Grrl.com and has written for such magazines as ''AuctionRover, BUST, Digit, Geek Monthly, Organic Gardening, Wired, Yahoo! Internet Life,'' and a myriad of zines.

==Biography==
Bonnie Burton is a former writer for The Official Star Wars Blog. She used the handle "bonniegrrl"<ref name="Blog">{{Blog|listing=true|bonniegrrl|Droids Just Wanna Have Fun|Bonnie Burton}}</ref> on those and other sites. At StarWars.com, Burton maintained the kids section that includes drawing tutorials, original crafts and fun educational articles, and she created the Star Wars Rocks section where she interviewed bands, actors, authors, and celebrities about their love for the films.

On [[May 7]], [[2012]], Burton tweeted that Lucasfilm had laid her off.<ref name="Laidoff">{{Twitter|bonniegrrl|status/199560439175188480|Bonnie Burton|quote=Lucasfilm laid me off. Contact me for full-time & freelance writing/social media gigs. Thanks! My CV:|archivefile=File:BonnieBurton-LaidOff.png}}</ref>

===Celebration V===
Burton's "marriage" to [[R2-D2]] at [[Celebration V]] earned considerable attention and was featured in a video on the Official Site.<ref name="BonnieWeddingVideo">{{SWArchive|url=video/view/001071.html|text=Video}}</ref> In a ceremony at the Celebration Chapel, Darth Maul presided, Darth Vader was R2-D2's best man,<ref name="BonnieR2Tweet1">{{Twitter|bonniegrrl|status/39123271303704576|Bonnie Burton|quote=@erier2003: R2-D2's best man at the wedding was Darth Vader. C-3PO is never gonna forgive me for that one.|archivedate=20161119160646}}</ref> model and ''Star Wars'' fan Adrienne Curry was a bridesmaid, and Lucasfilm's [[Stephen J. Sansweet]] gave Burton away. The two have an "open-source" marriage,<ref name="BonnieR2Tweet2">{{Twitter|bonniegrrl|status/38857925837590528|Bonnie Burton|quote=@Alyssa_Milano: R2-D2 & I have an Open Source Marriage. I can still see other humans. ;-)|archiveurl=https://archive.vn/fcWP8}}</ref> and according to Burton, "Exchanging restraining bolts is much more romantic than exchanging rings."<ref name="BonnieR2Tweet3">{{Twitter|bonniegrrl|status/39122332266139648|Bonnie Burton|quote=@erier2003: exchanging restraining bolts is much more romantic than exchanging rings. ;-)|archivedate=20161016231057}}</ref> Burton also wrote about the history of her relationship with the astromech droid on The Official Star Wars Blog.<ref name="BonnieR2SWBlog">{{OfficialBlog|url=2010/08/18/romancing-the-droid-why-i-married-r2-d2|text=Romancing the Droid: Why I Married R2-D2}}</ref>

